Definition:
Inheritance is the process by which one class acquires the properties and methods of another class using the extends keyword.

Syntax
class Animal {
    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Animal Sound");
    }
}

class Dog extends Animal {
    void bark() {
        System.out.println("Bark");
    }
}
Main
Dog d = new Dog();

d.sound();   // Parent class method
d.bark();    // Child class method
Important Points ⭐
✅ Uses extends keyword.
✅ Parent class is called Superclass.
✅ Child class is called Subclass.
✅ Child inherits variables and methods of parent.
✅ Promotes Code Reusability.
✅ Java supports Single, Multilevel, and Hierarchical inheritance (not multiple inheritance with classes).
Benefits
♻️ Code Reusability
📖 Easy to maintain
🚀 Less code duplication
